<subSubSection pageId="211" pageNumber="212" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="211" pageNumber="212">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="211" pageNumber="212">
First mentioned as nomen nudum in 
<bibRefCitation author="Peres, J-M" journalOrPublisher="Journal de Conchyliologie" pageId="326" pageNumber="327" pagination="129 - 162" refId="B422" refString="Peres, J-M, 1939. Contribution a l'etude des Melanopsis du Maroc. Journal de Conchyliologie 83: 129 - 162" title="Contribution a l'etude des Melanopsis du Maroc." volume="83" year="1939">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Pérès">Peres</normalizedToken>
(1939)
</bibRefCitation>
, but described and made available by 
<bibRefCitation author="Peres, J-M" journalOrPublisher="Journal de Conchyliologie" pageId="326" pageNumber="327" pagination="109 - 136" refId="B423" refString="Peres, J-M, 1946. Contribution a l'etude du genre Melanopsis. Journal de Conchyliologie 86 (3-4): 109 - 136" title="Contribution a l'etude du genre Melanopsis." volume="86" year="1946">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Pérès">Peres</normalizedToken>
(1946)
</bibRefCitation>
. In both works 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Pérès">Peres</normalizedToken>
obviously used the name not as a separate taxon but rather as descriptive term to fit existing species into his morphological concept. The name is in fact a junior objective synonym of several different species.
</paragraph>
